ix commit'.","test_description":"Seed state with latest fix commit C2 and last review round tied to older commit C1. Attempt PASS finalization and assert block. Then create a new review round linked to C2 (or newer) and assert PASS can proceed when other gates are satisfied.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pairwise: Integration beats Unit (state handoff across loop stages). Integration vs System: real OS/network is not the primary boundary. Agentic beats Integration because behavior explicitly requires a real review-agent round in the live loop; a stubbed agent can falsely satisfy 'ran' while hiding failures tied to actual model execution outcomes/termination in-loop. Agentic vs Workflow: this behavior requires one fresh agent round gating PASS, not exhaustion across multiple rounds. Rejection gate: Workflow rejected because behavior text specifies a fresh round requirement, not multi-round sequencing outcomes.","test_description":"Run the live loop against an updated diff with real review-agent invocation enabled. Verify PASS finalization is denied until a post-fix agent round completes and is linked to that diff/commit; then verify finalization can continue only after that fresh round record exists.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.58,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pairwise: Integration beats Unit because exhaustion counters + stored MUST-FIX findings must be combined across modu